tency of the `transpose_to_\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:56:05.483Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"key` implementation, and then commit the report.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_use\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:56:06.069Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"write_file\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"write_file_1777164966069_0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"parameters\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"file_path\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sdp/verification/t-019 @20260425t183959z-verify.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"# Verification Report — T-019 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260425T183959Z_1777164786.log\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Date:** 2026-04-26\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/harmonic_planner.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `ESCALATIONS.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Correctness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe implementation of `transpose_to_key(record, key_name) -> int` correctly computes the smallest semitone offset required to align a sample's detected pitch with the nearest in-key pitch class. It handles the octave wrap correctly by searching in both directions. The tie-breaking logic favors negative transposition, which is consistent and verified by tests.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Completeness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAll acceptance criteria are met:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Transposition maps `pitch_hz` to the nearest in-key pitch using the artist's B-rooted palette.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Samples with `pitch_confidence < 0.4` or `pitch_hz <= 0` return 0 semitones, correctly playing \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"atonally\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Tests cover known pitch/key combinations, low-confidence pass-through, and octave wrap shortest-path selection.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe implementation leverages `harmonic_planner.py` for canonical key normalization and scale definitions, ensuring consistency with the rest of the SenseWeave harmony engine. The coding style and test patterns match the existing codebase.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nNo security vulnerabilities were identified. The implementation uses standard math libraries and does not involve unsafe operations or credential handling.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe code is concise, well-documented, and follows idiomatic Python patterns. The tests are comprehensive and use appropriate fixtures (standard within the project). Mandatory hardening checks regarding `bootstrap_identity` were found to be already addressed in the daemon startup flows (`daemon.py` and `cypherclaw_daemon.py`).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- [x] (Minor/Environmental) `pytest tests/ -x` encountered a `PermissionError` in `test_daemon_fallback.py` due to macOS Seatbelt restrictions on `~/.promptclaw/pets.json`. This is an environmental constraint unrelated to the T-019 changes. Focused tests for the new implementation (`tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py`) passed successfully.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe implementation is solid and integrates well with the established harmonic planning utilities. No further actions required for this task.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_result\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:56:06.240Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"write_file_1777164966069_0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:56:08.350Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I will stage the verification report and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:56:08.353Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" commit it with a clear message to finalize the verification of task T-019.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_use\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:56:08.353Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command_1777164968353_0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"parameters\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"git add \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sdp/verification/t-019 @20260425t183959z-verify.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" && git commit -m \\\