2 test(sample-capture): canned dogs and transient-cluster WAV fixtures [T-015@20260425T183959Zb]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n72b395c verify(T-015): verification report — PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n8967ae4 test(sample-capture): canned WAV fixtures for detector branches [T-015@20260425T183959Za]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n696db88 verify(T-017): verification report — PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n85e9b3e feat(duet-composer): per-mode sampler density gates [T-017@20260425T183959Z]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n4d26171 verify(T-012@20260425T183959Zd): verification report — PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n .github/workflows/detector-smoke.yml               | 33 ++++++++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n progress.md                                        | 20 +++--\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n .../Lead_T-012_20260425T183959Zc_1777159697.log    |  1 +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n sdp/notifications.log                              |  9 +++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n sdp/run-log.md                                     |  9 +++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n sdp/verification/t-015@20260425t183959zc-verify.md | 50 +++++++++++++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n tests/fixtures/audio/README.md                     | 55 ++++++++++++++\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py                | 87 ++++++++--------------\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n 8 files changed, 201 insertions(+), 63 deletions(-)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:47:01.450Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I will\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:47:01.557Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" now examine the GitHub workflow configuration and the fixture documentation to ensure they meet the task requirements, while also checking for any flagged\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:47:01.770Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" issues in the escalations log.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_use\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:47:02.152Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command_1777164422152_0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"parameters\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"description\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Reading CI configuration, fixture documentation, and escalations.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"cat .github/workflows/detector-smoke.yml && cat tests/fixtures/audio/README.md && cat ESCALATIONS.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_result\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:47:02.337Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command_1777164422152_0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"name: detector-branch-smoke\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\non:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  push:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    branches: [\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  pull_request:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\njobs:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  detector-branch-smoke:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    timeout-minutes: 5\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    steps:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      - name: Set up Python\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        uses: actions/setup-python@v5\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        with:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n          python-version: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"3.11\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n          cache: pip\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      - name: Install package + dev extras\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        run: |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n          python -m pip install --upgrade pip\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n          pip install -e '.[dev]'\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      - name: Detector-branch smoke test (canned WAV fixtures, <30s)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        run: |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n          # Wall-clock guard: the smoke job must finish in <30s.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n          timeout 30 python -m pytest \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            -k \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"fixture or smoke\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            -x --tb=short --durations=10\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n# Canned audio fixtures\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nDeterministic 1-second mono 16-bit PCM WAV files at 8 kHz, used by the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndetector-branch smoke test in `tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py` to\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nexercise `InterestingMomentDetector` without depending on JACK or live\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ncapture.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| Fixture | Detector branch | Seed |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| `silence.wav` | baseline; must not flag | — |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| `dishwasher.wav` | steady hum baseline; must not flag | 7 |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| `footsteps.wav` | broadband transients | 11 |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| `music.wav` | tonal pad + plucks | (deterministic) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| `dogs.wav` | bark-style tonal bursts | 17 |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| `transient_cluster.wav` | dense transient cluster | 23 |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Regenerating the fixtures\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe generator lives next to the WAVs at `generate.py`. It uses fixed RNG\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nseeds, so the bytes on disk are reproducible across machines as long as\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nNumPy's `default_rng` stream is stable.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\npython tests/fixtures/audio/generate.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThat rewrites every fixture in this directory in place. To refresh only\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\none fixture, edit its generator function (e.g. `dogs()`) and rerun the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nscript — non-edited fixtures regenerate to identical bytes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## When to regenerate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- The synthesis parameters in `generate.py` change (frequencies,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  envelopes, burst counts, durations).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `SAMPLE_RATE` or `DURATION_SECONDS` change.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- A new detector branch needs a dedicated fixture (add a generator,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  register it in `FIXTURES`, rerun, then add a parametrize case in\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  `test_detector_branch_smoke_test_flags_on_matching_fixture`).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAfter regenerating, run the smoke test locally before committing:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\npytest tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py -k \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"fixture or smoke\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe same selector runs in the `detector-branch-smoke` GitHub Actions\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\njob (`.github/workflows/detector-smoke.yml`), which is wall-clock\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nbounded to 30 seconds.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Format invariants\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAll fixtures must be mono, 16-bit PCM, 8 kHz, exactly 1 second long.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`test_canned_fixtures_are_one_second_at_eight_kilohertz` enforces this\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\non every run; if it fails after a regen, check that you did not change\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`SAMPLE_RATE` or `DURATION_SECONDS` without updating the test.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n# Escalations\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nItems requiring human review. Append-only per task.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## T-001 (2026-04-01T18:55:24.984659+00:00)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Reason:** Agent timeout\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Details:** T-001 timed out twice. Run sdp-cli tasks split T-001 to break it down.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## T-001 (2026-04-01T18:56:11.434931+00:00)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Reason:** Agent timeout\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Details:** T-001 timed out twice. Run sdp-cli tasks split T-001 to break it down.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## T-001 (2026-04-01T18:56:41.692113+00:00)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Reason:** Agent timeout\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Details:** T-001 timed out twice. Run sdp-cli tasks split T-001 to break it down.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## T-009@20260408T220341Z (2026-04-08T22:12:54.185469+00:00)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Reason:** Ordered degradation policy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Details:** step-1: reason=verify-first tier cascade: promoted verify-tier model as lead; original_pair=claude->codex; degraded_pair=codex->claude; remaining_headroom=85.0%\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nstep-2: reason=effort-first lead-tier downgrade applied (codex effort xhigh -> high) before family/version fallback; original_pair=codex->claude; degraded_pair=codex->claude; remaining_headroom=85.0%\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nstep-3: reason=same-provider verify fallback attempted but no same-provider verify candidate was available; original_pair=codex->claude; degraded_pair=codex->clau