convergence in `artist_identity.py` as still pending so it does not overstate completion. Cross-links to the upstream PRD (`my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md`) and the musicianship roadmap (`docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md`) keep the artistic intent and the longer status snapshot in their canonical homes rather than duplicating them here. No new dependencies, no migrations, and no runtime code changes are required. The auto-generated hardening items referencing `bootstrap_identity()` invocation, `FirstBootAnnouncer` sequencing, standalone/federated coverage, and startup integration tests are out of scope for a documentation subtask: the `bootstrap_identity()` invocation already lives in `sample_capture_daemon.py::main` and the startup paths are already covered by `tests/test_first_boot.py` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py`. This mirrors the established out-of-scope escalation pattern from T-008@20260425T183959Zd and the sibling T-013@20260425T183959Za. The artistic-intent companion document (`docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md`) is the remaining CCS-033 sibling and is left for a follow-up subtask.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## T-013@20260425T183959Zc (2026-04-25T19:10:00Z)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Reason:** Artistic-intent documentation scope and generated-progress constraint\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Details:** Exploration confirmed that CCS-033's remaining work is the one-page artistic-intent companion at `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md`. The sampler PRD (`my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md`) remains the canonical source for the three usages and five principles; the new page will restate that intent in a shorter listener-facing form focused on aesthetic goals, the sampler's role inside the quintet, and the intended listener experience, while cross-linking the PRD, the roadmap, and the architecture document instead of duplicating their implementation detail. This subtask is documentation-only: no runtime code changes, no migrations, and no new dependencies are required. The generated candidate hardening items about `revise_score()` integration, resource-governor budget enforcement, and `bootstrap_identity()` sequencing are out of scope for this doc task and were verified as unrelated to the affected files. Because `progress.md` is generated and already contains unrelated in-flight state changes, its exploration update is limited to the single T-013@20260425T183959Zc task line rather than a broader manual rewrite.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## T-014@20260425T183959Za (2026-04-25T19:30:00Z)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Reason:** Service-wiring assumptions and generated-hardening scope\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Details:** Exploration mapped `CCS-020` to the current tree: `my-claw/systemd/` has no `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`, `cypherclaw_boot.sh` does not yet start that service, and existing CypherClaw units consistently run as `User=user` from `/home/user/cypherclaw` with the project virtualenv at `/home/user/cypherclaw/.venv/bin/python3`. The repo references `cypherclaw-jack.service` from other units but does not define that unit locally, so this task assumes it is a host-managed prerequisite and wires the dependency without inventing a second JACK service. No new dependencies or migrations are required. The auto-generated `bootstrap_identity()` hardening items are already covered elsewhere in the current tree; because this task touches boot/service startup, the existing startup identity tests will be re-run as verification anchors rather than reworking unrelated startup code.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## T-014@20260425T183959Zc (2026-04-25T23:05:00Z)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Reason:** Live systemd verification host assumption\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Details:** Exploration confirmed that this checkout is running on macOS and does not provide local `systemctl`, while the target Linux host is reachable as `cypherclaw` over non-interactive SSH. This task will add a repo-backed verifier tool that supports both local Linux execution and `--host cypherclaw` remote execution, then use that remote path for the real `kill -9` / restart validation. No new dependencies or migrations are required.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:47:04.075Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I will examine the updates in the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:47:04.091Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" sample capture daemon tests to verify that the smoke tests and canned fixtures have been correctly implemented.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_use\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:47:04.119Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command_1777164424119_0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"parameters\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"cat tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"description\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Reading the test file.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\n++{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_result\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-26T00:47:04.308Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command_1777164424119_0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Tests for sample_capture_daemon.py.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom __future__ import annotations\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport logging\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport os\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport sqlite3\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport sys\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport wave\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom collections.abc import Callable\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport numpy as np\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport pytest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nsys.path.insert(0, os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"my-claw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tools\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom sample_capture_daemon import (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    ARC_PHASES,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    BUFFER_DURATION_SECONDS,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    JACK_INPUT_PORTS,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    JACK_SOURCE_PORTS,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    MOOD_LABELS,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    PRESENCE_LABELS,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    SAMPLE_RATE,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    SELF_QUOTE_DURATION_SECONDS,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    AcousticFeatures,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    AcousticTagThresholds,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    DetectorThresholds,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    InterestingMomentDetector,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    SampleCaptureDaemon,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    SampleTags,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    analyze_acoustic_features,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    build_sample_tags,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    derive_acoustic_tags,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    extract_context_tags,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    save_capture,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    self_quote,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    time_of_day_from_timestamp,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nclass _FakeInputPort:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def __init__(self, name: str) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self.name = name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self._frames = np.zeros(0, dtype=np.float32)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def get_array(self) -> np.ndarray:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        return self._frames\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def set_frames(self, frames: np.ndarray) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self._frames = np.asarray(frames, dtype=np.float32)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nclass _FakeInputPorts:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def __init__(self) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self._ports: dict[str, _FakeInputPort] = {}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def register(self, name: str) -> _FakeInputPort:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        port = _FakeInputPort(name)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self._ports[name] = port\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        return port\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nclass _FakeJackClient:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def __init__(self, name: str) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self.name = name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self.inports = _FakeInputPorts()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self.connections: list[tuple[str, str]] = []\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self.activated = False\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self.closed = False\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self._process_callback: Callable[[int], object] | None = None\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self._xrun_callback: Callable[[float], object] | None = None\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def set_process_callback(self, callback: Callable[[int], object]) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self._process_callback = callback\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def set_xrun_callback(self, callback: Callable[[float], object]) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self._xrun_callback = callback\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def activate(self) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self.activated = True\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def connect(self, source: str, destination: _FakeInputPort) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self.connections.append((source, f\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"{self.name}:{destination.name}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def close(self) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self.closed = True\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def push_frames(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        contact: np.ndarray,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        room: np.ndarray,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self_frames: np.ndarray | None = None,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    ) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self.inports._ports[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"in_contact\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"].set_frames(contact)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self.inports._ports[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"in_room\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"].set_frames(room)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        if \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"in_self\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in self.inports._ports:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            self.inports._ports[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"in_self\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"].set_frames(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                np.zeros(len(contact), dtype=np.float32) if self_frames is None else self_frames\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        assert self._process_callback is not None\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self._process_callback(len(contact))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def push_self_frames(self, frames: np.ndarray) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self.inports._ports[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"in_contact\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"].set_frames(np.zeros(len(frames), dtype=np.float32))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self.inports._ports[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"in_room\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"].set_frames(np.zeros(len(frames), dtype=np.float32))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self.inports._ports[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"in_self\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"].set_frames(np.asarray(frames, dtype=np.float32))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        assert self._process_callback is not None\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self._process_callback(len(frames))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def trigger_xrun(self, delay_usecs: float = 0.0) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        assert self._xrun_callback is not None\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        self._xrun_callback(delay_usecs)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef _start_daemon(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    *,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    sample_rate: int = 4,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    buffer_duration_seconds: int = 3,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n) -> tuple[SampleCaptureDaemon, _FakeJackClient]:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    client = _FakeJackClient(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"cypherclaw-capture\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    daemon = SampleCaptureDaemon(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        sample_rate=sample_rate,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        buffer_duration_seconds=buffer_duration_seconds,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        client_factory=lambda _name: client,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    daemon.start()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    return daemon, client\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_defaults_match_prd_contract() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert SAMPLE_RATE == 48_000\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert BUFFER_DURATION_SECONDS == 60\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_start_registers_and_connects_expected_jack_ports() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    daemon, client = _start_daemon()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert client.activated is True\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert set(client.inports._ports) == {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"in_contact\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"in_room\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"in_self\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert client.connections == [\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        (JACK_SOURCE_PORTS[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"contact\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"], \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"cypherclaw-capture:in_contact\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        (JACK_SOURCE_PORTS[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"], \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"cypherclaw-capture:in_room\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        (JACK_SOURCE_PORTS[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"self\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"], \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"cypherclaw-capture:in_self\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    ]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert daemon.input_port_names == JACK_INPUT_PORTS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert JACK_SOURCE_PORTS[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"self\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"] == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"SuperCollider:out_1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_ring_buffer_retains_latest_rolling_window() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    daemon, client = _start_daemon()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    for start in range(0, 16, 4):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        client.push_frames(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            np.arange(start, start + 4, dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            np.arange(100 + start, 104 + start, dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    np.testing.assert_array_equal(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        daemon.get_window(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"contact\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", duration_sec=3.0, offset_sec=0.0),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        np.arange(4, 16, dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    np.testing.assert_array_equal(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        daemon.get_window(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", duration_sec=3.0, offset_sec=0.0),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        np.arange(104, 116, dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_get_window_supports_offsets_and_zero_padding() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    daemon, client = _start_daemon(sample_rate=4, buffer_duration_seconds=8)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    client.push_frames(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        np.arange(20, dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        np.arange(200, 220, dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    np.testing.assert_array_equal(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        daemon.get_window(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"contact\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", duration_sec=1.5, offset_sec=1.0),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        np.arange(10, 16, dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    np.testing.assert_array_equal(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        daemon.get_window(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", duration_sec=2.0, offset_sec=4.0),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        np.array([0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 201, 202, 203], dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nFIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE = 8000\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef _silence(seconds: float, sample_rate: int = FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE) -> np.ndarray:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    return np.zeros(int(round(seconds * sample_rate)), dtype=np.float32)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef _hum(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    seconds: float,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    sample_rate: int = FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    *,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    base_freq: float = 110.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n) -> np.ndarray:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    n = int(round(seconds * sample_rate))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    t = np.arange(n, dtype=np.float32) / sample_rate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    rng = np.random.default_rng(7)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    samples = (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        0.08 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * base_freq * t)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        + 0.05 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * (base_freq * 2.0) * t)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        + 0.03 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * (base_freq * 3.0) * t)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        + 0.01 * rng.standard_normal(n).astype(np.float32)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    return samples.astype(np.float32)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef _footsteps(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    seconds: float,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    sample_rate: int = FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    *,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    count: int = 5,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n) -> np.ndarray:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    n = int(round(seconds * sample_rate))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    samples = np.zeros(n, dtype=np.float32)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    rng = np.random.default_rng(11)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    burst_len = int(round(0.04 * sample_rate))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    envelope = np.exp(-np.linspace(0.0, 6.0, burst_len, dtype=np.float32))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    spacing = (n - burst_len) / max(1, count + 1)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    for i in range(count):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        start = int(round(spacing * (i + 1)))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        burst = (rng.standard_normal(burst_len).astype(np.float32) * 0.35) * envelope\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        samples[start : start + burst_len] += burst\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    return samples\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef _music(seconds: float, sample_rate: int = FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE) -> np.ndarray:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    n = int(round(seconds * sample_rate))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    t = np.arange(n, dtype=np.float32) / sample_rate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    pad = 0.04 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * 220.0 * t) + 0.03 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * 330.0 * t)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    samples = pad.astype(np.float32)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    pluck_period = 0.18\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    pluck_dur = int(round(0.06 * sample_rate))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    env = np.exp(-np.linspace(0.0, 7.0, pluck_dur, dtype=np.float32))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    pluck_count = int(seconds / pluck_period)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    for i in range(pluck_count):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        start = int(round(i * pluck_period * sample_rate))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        if start + pluck_dur > n:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            break\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        freq = 440.0 + (i * 67.0) % 240.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        local_t = np.arange(pluck_dur, dtype=np.float32) / sample_rate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        samples[start : start + pluck_dur] += (0.4 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * freq * local_t) * env).astype(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            np.float32\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    return samples\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef _make_detector(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    *,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    thresholds: DetectorThresholds | None = None,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    sample_rate: int = FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    clock: Callable[[], float] | None = None,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n) -> InterestingMomentDetector:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    return InterestingMomentDetector(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        source=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        sample_rate=sample_rate,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        thresholds=thresholds,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        clock=clock,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_detector_thresholds_match_prd_defaults() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    thresholds = DetectorThresholds()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert thresholds.spectral_flux_multiplier == 0.6\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert thresholds.rms_dbfs_floor == -45.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert thresholds.transient_count_min == 2\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert thresholds.cooldown_seconds == 30.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert thresholds.window_seconds == 1.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert thresholds.hop_seconds == 0.25\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert thresholds.min_capture_seconds == 4.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert thresholds.max_capture_seconds == 8.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_detector_thresholds_from_env_overrides() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    overrides = DetectorThresholds.from_env(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"SAMPLE_CAPTURE_FLUX_MULTIPLIER\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"0.4\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"SAMPLE_CAPTURE_RMS_DBFS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"-30\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"SAMPLE_CAPTURE_TRANSIENT_MIN\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"3\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"SAMPLE_CAPTURE_COOLDOWN_SEC\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"5\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"SAMPLE_CAPTURE_MAX_LEN_SEC\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"9\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        }\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert overrides.spectral_flux_multiplier == 0.4\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert overrides.rms_dbfs_floor == -30.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert overrides.transient_count_min == 3\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert overrides.cooldown_seconds == 5.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert overrides.max_capture_seconds == 9.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert overrides.window_seconds == DetectorThresholds().window_seconds\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_detector_silence_does_not_flag() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    detector = _make_detector(clock=iter([0.0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0]).__next__)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    flagged = [detector.evaluate(_silence(1.0)) for _ in range(5)]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert flagged == [None, None, None, None, None]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_detector_dishwasher_hum_does_not_flag_due_to_no_transients() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    detector = _make_detector(clock=iter([0.0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0]).__next__)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    results = [detector.evaluate(_hum(1.0)) for _ in range(5)]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert all(r is None for r in results), \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"steady hum lacks transient density\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_detector_footsteps_flag_after_baseline() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    times = iter([0.0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0]).__next__\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    detector = _make_detector(clock=times)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    for _ in range(2):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        detector.evaluate(_silence(1.0))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    detector.evaluate(_hum(1.0))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    flagged = detector.evaluate(_footsteps(1.0))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert flagged is not None\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert flagged.transient_count >= 2\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert flagged.rms_dbfs > -45.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert 4.0 <= flagged.capture_seconds <= 8.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert flagged.pre_roll_seconds + flagged.post_roll_seconds == pytest.approx(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        flagged.capture_seconds - 1.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_detector_music_flags_and_capture_window_within_bounds() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    times = iter([0.0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0, 1.25]).__next__\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    detector = _make_detector(clock=times)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    for _ in range(3):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        detector.evaluate(_hum(1.0))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    flagged = detector.evaluate(_music(1.0))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert flagged is not None\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert flagged.transient_count >= 2\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert 4.0 <= flagged.capture_seconds <= 8.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_detector_cooldown_suppresses_back_to_back_flags() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    times = [0.0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0, 31.0, 31.25]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    detector = _make_detector(clock=iter(times).__next__)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    for _ in range(3):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        detector.evaluate(_silence(1.0))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    first = detector.evaluate(_footsteps(1.0))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    second = detector.evaluate(_footsteps(1.0))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    detector.evaluate(_silence(1.0))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    third = detector.evaluate(_footsteps(1.0))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert first is not None\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert second is None, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"second flag inside cooldown should be suppressed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert third is not None, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"third flag past cooldown should fire again\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAUDIO_FIXTURE_DIR = Path(__file__).resolve().parent / \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"fixtures\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" / \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"audio\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAUDIO_FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE = 8000\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef _read_fixture_wav(name: str) -> np.ndarray:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    path = AUDIO_FIXTURE_DIR / name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    with wave.open(str(path), \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rb\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") as handle:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        assert handle.getnchannels() == 1, f\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"{name} must be mono\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        assert handle.getframerate() == AUDIO_FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE, (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            f\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"{name} must be {AUDIO_FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE} Hz\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        assert handle.getsampwidth() == 2, f\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"{name} must be 16-bit\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        nframes = handle.getnframes()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        raw = handle.readframes(nframes)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    pcm = np.frombuffer(raw, dtype=np.int16)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    return pcm.astype(np.float32) / 32767.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_canned_fixtures_are_one_second_at_eight_kilohertz() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    for name in (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"silence.wav\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"dishwasher.wav\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"footsteps.wav\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"music.wav\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"dogs.wav\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"transient_cluster.wav\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    ):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        samples = _read_fixture_wav(name)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        assert samples.shape == (AUDIO_FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE,), (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            f\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"{name} should contain exactly 1 second of audio\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@pytest.fixture\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef canned_window() -> Callable[[str], np.ndarray]:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    def _loader(name: str) -> np.ndarray:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        if not name.endswith(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".wav\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            name += \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".wav\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        return _read_fixture_wav(name)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    return _loader\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_silence_fixture_does_not_flag_detector(canned_window: Callable[[str], np.ndarray]) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    detector = _make_detector(clock=iter([0.0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0]).__next__)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    samples = canned_window(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"silence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    flagged = [detector.evaluate(samples) for _ in range(5)]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert flagged == [None, None, None, None, None]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_dishwasher_fixture_does_not_flag_detector(canned_window: Callable[[str], np.ndarray]) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    detector = _make_detector(clock=iter([0.0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0]).__next__)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    samples = canned_window(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"dishwasher\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    results = [detector.evaluate(samples) for _ in range(5)]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert all(r is None for r in results), \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"steady hum lacks transient density\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"fixture_name, expected_min_transients\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    [\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"footsteps\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", 2),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"music\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", 2),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"dogs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", 2),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"transient_cluster\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", 4),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    ],\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_detector_branch_smoke_test_flags_on_matching_fixture(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    canned_window: Callable[[str], np.ndarray],\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    fixture_name: str,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    expected_min_transients: int,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    times = iter([0.0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0, 1.25]).__next__\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    detector = _make_detector(clock=times)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    # Warm up the detector with a steady hum to establish a baseline\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    hum_samples = canned_window(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"dishwasher\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    for _ in range(3):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        detector.evaluate(hum_samples)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    flagged = detector.evaluate(canned_window(fixture_name))\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert flagged is not None\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert flagged.transient_count >= expected_min_transients\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert flagged.rms_dbfs > -45.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_detector_step_pulls_window_from_daemon() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    daemon, client = _start_daemon(sample_rate=FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE, buffer_duration_seconds=2)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    chunk = FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE // 4\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    for _ in range(4):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        client.push_frames(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            np.zeros(chunk, dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            np.zeros(chunk, dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    detector = InterestingMomentDetector(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        daemon=daemon,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        source=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        thresholds=DetectorThresholds(window_seconds=1.0, transient_count_min=1),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        clock=iter([0.0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75]).__next__,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    for _ in range(3):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        detector.step()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    footsteps = _footsteps(1.0, FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    half = footsteps.size // 2\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    client.push_frames(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        np.zeros(half, dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        footsteps[:half],\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    client.push_frames(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        np.zeros(footsteps.size - half, dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        footsteps[half:],\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    flagged = detector.step()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert flagged is not None\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert flagged.transient_count >= 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_xrun_logs_warning_and_capture_continues(caplog) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    daemon, client = _start_daemon(sample_rate=4, buffer_duration_seconds=3)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    caplog.set_level(logging.WARNING)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    client.push_frames(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        np.array([1, 2, 3, 4], dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        np.array([11, 12, 13, 14], dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    client.trigger_xrun(128.0)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    client.push_frames(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        np.array([5, 6, 7, 8], dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        np.array([15, 16, 17, 18], dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert daemon.xrun_count == 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"xrun\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in caplog.text.lower()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    np.testing.assert_array_equal(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        daemon.get_window(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"contact\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", duration_sec=2.0, offset_sec=0.0),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8], dtype=np.float32),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_extract_context_tags_normalizes_full_snapshot() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    # 2026-04-25 14:30 PDT (≈ 2026-04-25 21:30 UTC) — afternoon bucket\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    captured_at = 1777152600.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    context = {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"organism\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arc_phase\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Climax\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mode\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"engaged\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mood\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"label\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"valence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.42, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arousal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.7},\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        },\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room_presence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"someone_here\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": True,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"confidence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.88,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        },\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    }\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    tags = extract_context_tags(context, captured_at=captured_at)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert isinstance(tags, SampleTags)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.arc_phase == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"climax\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.mood_label == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.mood_valence == pytest.approx(0.42)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.mood_arousal == pytest.approx(0.7)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.presence == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"engaged\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.presence_confidence == pytest.approx(0.88)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.someone_here is True\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.time_of_day in TIME_OF_DAY_LABELS_LOCAL\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.captured_at_unix == captured_at\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.captured_at_iso.endswith(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") and \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"T\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in tags.captured_at_iso\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_extract_context_tags_handles_missing_and_invalid_values() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    captured_at = 1777152600.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    tags = extract_context_tags(None, captured_at=captured_at)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.arc_phase == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"unknown\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.mood_label == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"neutral\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.mood_valence == 0.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.mood_arousal == 0.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.presence == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"unknown\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.presence_confidence == 0.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.someone_here is False\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.captured_at_unix == captured_at\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    bad = {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"organism\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arc_phase\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"intermission\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mode\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"lurking\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mood\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"label\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"thrilled\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"valence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"n/a\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arousal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": float(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"nan\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")},\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        },\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room_presence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"confidence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 5.0, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"someone_here\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"yes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"},\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    }\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    tags = extract_context_tags(bad, captured_at=captured_at)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.arc_phase == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"unknown\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.presence == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"unknown\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.mood_label == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"neutral\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.mood_valence == 0.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.mood_arousal == 0.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.presence_confidence == 1.0  # clamped to [0, 1]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.someone_here is True\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_extract_context_tags_falls_back_to_top_level_keys() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    context = {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arc_phase\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mood\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"label\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"melancholy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"valence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": -0.5, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arousal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.2},\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"presence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"presence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"solo\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"confidence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.6, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"someone_here\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": False},\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    }\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    tags = extract_context_tags(context, captured_at=0.0)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.arc_phase == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.mood_label == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"melancholy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.mood_valence == pytest.approx(-0.5)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.presence == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"solo\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.presence_confidence == pytest.approx(0.6)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.someone_here is False\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_sample_tags_as_dict_round_trips_all_fields() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    tags = extract_context_tags(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"organism\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arc_phase\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"build\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}, captured_at=1777152600.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    payload = tags.as_dict()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    expected_keys = {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arc_phase\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mood_label\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mood_valence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mood_arousal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"presence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"presence_confidence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"someone_here\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"time_of_day\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"captured_at_iso\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"captured_at_unix\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"acoustic_tags\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mode\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"extra_tags\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    }\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert set(payload) == expected_keys\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert payload[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arc_phase\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"] == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"build\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert payload[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"acoustic_tags\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"] == []\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert payload[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mode\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"] == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"unknown\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert payload[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"extra_tags\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"] == {}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_time_of_day_buckets_cover_full_day() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    # Build local-time fixtures for representative hours.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    import datetime as _dt\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    base = _dt.datetime(2026, 4, 25, 0, 0, 0)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    hours_to_label = {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        2: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"night\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        7: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"dawn\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        10: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"morning\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        14: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"afternoon\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        18: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"evening\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        22: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"night\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    }\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    for hour, label in hours_to_label.items():\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        ts = (base.replace(hour=hour)).timestamp()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        assert time_of_day_from_timestamp(ts) == label\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_known_label_sets_match_documented_schema() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert ARC_PHASES == {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"build\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rise\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"climax\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"resolve\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert PRESENCE_LABELS == {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"solo\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aware\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"engaged\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"performing\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert MOOD_LABELS == {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"melancholy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"neutral\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"anxious\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"excited\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    }\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nTIME_OF_DAY_LABELS_LOCAL = {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"night\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"dawn\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"morning\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"afternoon\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"evening\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_analyze_acoustic_features_handles_empty_and_silent_input() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    empty = analyze_acoustic_features(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        np.zeros(0, dtype=np.float32), FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert empty == AcousticFeatures()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    silent = analyze_acoustic_features(_silence(1.0), FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert silent.spectral_centroid_hz == 0.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert silent.spectral_bandwidth_hz == 0.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert silent.transient_density_hz == 0.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_analyze_acoustic_features_centroid_tracks_dominant_frequency() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    sample_rate = FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    n = sample_rate  # 1 second\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    t = np.arange(n, dtype=np.float32) / sample_rate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    low = (0.5 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * 220.0 * t)).astype(np.float32)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    high = (0.5 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * 2200.0 * t)).astype(np.float32)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    low_features = analyze_acoustic_features(low, sample_rate)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    high_features = analyze_acoustic_features(high, sample_rate)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert low_features.spectral_centroid_hz == pytest.approx(220.0, rel=0.05)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert high_features.spectral_centroid_hz == pytest.approx(2200.0, rel=0.05)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert high_features.spectral_centroid_hz > low_features.spectral_centroid_hz\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_analyze_acoustic_features_bandwidth_widens_with_broadband_noise() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    sample_rate = FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    n = sample_rate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    t = np.arange(n, dtype=np.float32) / sample_rate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    tone = (0.5 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * 1000.0 * t)).astype(np.float32)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    rng = np.random.default_rng(42)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    noise = (0.3 * rng.standard_normal(n)).astype(np.float32)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    tone_features = analyze_acoustic_features(tone, sample_rate)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    noise_features = analyze_acoustic_features(noise, sample_rate)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tone_features.spectral_bandwidth_hz >= 0.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert noise_features.spectral_bandwidth_hz > tone_features.spectral_bandwidth_hz\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_analyze_acoustic_features_transient_density_is_per_second() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    sample_rate = FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    two_sec_footsteps = _footsteps(2.0, sample_rate=sample_rate, count=6)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    features = analyze_acoustic_features(two_sec_footsteps, sample_rate)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert features.transient_density_hz > 0.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    # 6 bursts spread over 2 s should not exceed ~3 transients/sec.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert features.transient_density_hz <= 3.5\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_analyze_acoustic_features_as_dict_exposes_numeric_fields() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    features = analyze_acoustic_features(_hum(1.0), FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    payload = features.as_dict()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert set(payload) == {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"spectral_centroid_hz\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"spectral_bandwidth_hz\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"transient_density_hz\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    }\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert all(isinstance(v, float) for v in payload.values())\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_derive_acoustic_tags_silent_features_yield_no_tags() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert derive_acoustic_tags(AcousticFeatures()) == ()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_derive_acoustic_tags_low_centroid_low_transients_is_warm_and_sustained() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    features = AcousticFeatures(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        spectral_centroid_hz=300.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        spectral_bandwidth_hz=200.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        transient_density_hz=0.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert derive_acoustic_tags(features) == (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"warm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sustained\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_derive_acoustic_tags_narrow_high_centroid_is_bright_and_metallic() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    features = AcousticFeatures(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        spectral_centroid_hz=4000.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        spectral_bandwidth_hz=300.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        transient_density_hz=0.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    tags = derive_acoustic_tags(features)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"bright\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in tags\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"metallic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in tags\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"warm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" not in tags\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    # canonical order: bright before metallic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.index(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"bright\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") < tags.index(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"metallic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_derive_acoustic_tags_broadband_high_centroid_is_bright_not_metallic() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    features = AcousticFeatures(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        spectral_centroid_hz=3500.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        spectral_bandwidth_hz=1500.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        transient_density_hz=1.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    tags = derive_acoustic_tags(features)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"bright\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in tags\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"metallic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" not in tags\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_derive_acoustic_tags_high_transient_density_is_percussive_not_sustained() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    features = AcousticFeatures(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        spectral_centroid_hz=1000.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        spectral_bandwidth_hz=800.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        transient_density_hz=4.5,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    tags = derive_acoustic_tags(features)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"percussive\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in tags\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sustained\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" not in tags\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_derive_acoustic_tags_respects_custom_thresholds() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    features = AcousticFeatures(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        spectral_centroid_hz=500.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        spectral_bandwidth_hz=200.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        transient_density_hz=0.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    strict = AcousticTagThresholds(warm_centroid_max_hz=200.0)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"warm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" not in derive_acoustic_tags(features, thresholds=strict)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"warm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in derive_acoustic_tags(features)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_build_sample_tags_merges_context_and_acoustic_tags() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    sample_rate = FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    n = sample_rate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    t = np.arange(n, dtype=np.float32) / sample_rate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    warm_tone = (0.5 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * 220.0 * t)).astype(np.float32)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    tags = build_sample_tags(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        warm_tone,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        sample_rate,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        context={\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"organism\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arc_phase\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}},\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        captured_at=1777152600.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert isinstance(tags, SampleTags)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.arc_phase == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.captured_at_unix == 1777152600.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"warm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in tags.acoustic_tags\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"metallic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" not in tags.acoustic_tags\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    payload = tags.as_dict()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert payload[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"acoustic_tags\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"] == list(tags.acoustic_tags)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert payload[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arc_phase\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"] == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_build_sample_tags_silent_input_yields_empty_acoustic_tags() -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    tags = build_sample_tags(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        _silence(1.0),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        context=None,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        captured_at=0.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.acoustic_tags == ()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert tags.arc_phase == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"unknown\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_save_capture_emits_contextual_and_acoustic_tags_for_room_sample(tmp_path) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    sample_rate = FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    n = sample_rate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    t = np.arange(n, dtype=np.float32) / sample_rate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    warm_tone = (0.5 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * 220.0 * t)).astype(np.float32)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    captured_at = 1777152600.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    capture = save_capture(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        warm_tone,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        source=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        sample_rate=sample_rate,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        capture_root=tmp_path,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        context={\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"organism\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arc_phase\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mode\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"engaged\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mood\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"label\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"valence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.42, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arousal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.31},\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            },\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room_presence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"someone_here\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": True, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"confidence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.88},\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        },\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        captured_at=captured_at,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert capture.source == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert capture.path.exists()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert capture.path.parent == tmp_path / \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert capture.path.name.startswith(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room_20260425T213000Z_rest_\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert capture.tags.arc_phase == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert capture.tags.mood_label == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert capture.tags.presence == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"engaged\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert capture.tags.someone_here is True\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert capture.tags.time_of_day == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"afternoon\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert capture.tags.acoustic_tags == (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"warm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sustained\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    with wave.open(str(capture.path), \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rb\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") as handle:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        assert handle.getnchannels() == 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        assert handle.getframerate() == sample_rate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        assert handle.getsampwidth() == 3\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        assert handle.getnframes() == n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndef test_save_capture_persists_tags_to_sample_index(tmp_path) -> None:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    sample_rate = FIXTURE_SAMPLE_RATE\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    n = sample_rate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    t = np.arange(n, dtype=np.float32) / sample_rate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    warm_tone = (0.5 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * 220.0 * t)).astype(np.float32)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    capture = save_capture(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        warm_tone,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        source=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        sample_rate=sample_rate,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        capture_root=tmp_path,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        context={\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"organism\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arc_phase\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mode\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"engaged\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"mood\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"label\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"valence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.42, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arousal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.31},\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            },\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room_presence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"someone_here\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": True, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"confidence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.88},\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        },\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        captured_at=1777152600.0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    )\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    index_path = tmp_path / \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"index.sqlite\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert index_path.exists()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    with sqlite3.connect(index_path) as con:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        row = con.execute(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            SELECT source, path, arc_phase, mood_label, presence, someone_here,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n                   time_of_day, acoustic_tags_json, tags_json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            FROM samples\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            WHERE sample_id = ?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n            (capture.sample_id,),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n        ).fetchone()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert row is not None\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert row[0] == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"room\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert row[1] == str(capture.path)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert row[2] == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert row[3] == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert row[4] == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"engaged\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert row[5] == 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert row[6] == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"afternoon\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert json.loads(row[7]) == [\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"warm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sustained\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    payload = json.loads(row[8])\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert payload[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"arc_phase\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"] == \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"rest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    assert payload[\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"presence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"] == \\\\\\\\\\