d`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Include: problem statement, technical approach, edge cases, acceptance criteria.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Each acceptance criterion must have a VERIFY command.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Phase 2: Test Development\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Write tests BEFORE implementation, derived from the specification.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Tests must FAIL before implementation (Red phase).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- After this phase, test files are LOCKED — do not modify assertions.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Phase 3: Implement\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Implement the minimum code needed to pass all tests.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- One sub-task at a time, commit each logical unit.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Type hints on all function signatures.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Follow existing patterns.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Phase 4: Verify & Document\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Run full test suite and quality checks.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Update CHANGELOG.md, progress.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Rules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- No questions — document assumptions in ESCALATIONS.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Do not modify locked test assertions.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Log new dependencies to ESCALATIONS.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Commit per sub-task: `feat(scope): summary [T-022@20260416T054258Z]`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Common Pitfalls (from recurring verify feedback)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThese are the top reasons tasks get PASS WITH NOTES instead of clean PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAvoid them on the first attempt:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Always include a migration** when adding or modifying database columns.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  A new model or column without a migration is a deployment gap.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Commit all changes** before the verify phase begins. Uncommitted work\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  is flagged as blocking by the verifier.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Stay in scope** — only commit work under this task's ID. Do not bundle\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  changes from adjacent subtasks