CHANGELOG.md:5:- Added a weekly KL-divergence audit between the current IDyOM long-term model and an immutable week-0 snapshot (T-031): new `senseweave.generation.health.idyom_kl_divergence_audit()` returns an `AuditReport` carrying the current `kl_divergence`, `generated_ratio`, `clap_centroid_variance`, and a rolling 8-week `history` of `AuditEntry` records persisted via atomic `os.replace` at `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/state/idyom_kl_audit.json`. KL is symmetric (`0.5*(KL(P||Q)+KL(Q||P))`) over a Laplace-smoothed (`alpha=1.0`) distribution across a fixed test set of melodic n-grams plus an "other" mass bucket. Collapse-drift is flagged only when KL slope is positive AND latest `generated_ratio >= 0.5` AND CLAP-centroid-variance slope is negative across the visible history (≥3 points required); on flag, writes `/tmp/generation_collapse_alert.json` and never auto-rollbacks the LTM. Ships with `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-idyom-kl-audit.{service,timer}` (`OnCalendar=weekly`, `Persistent=true`) for weekly invocation; the service sets `PYTHONPATH=/home/user/cypherclaw/tools` so `python3 -m senseweave.generation.health` resolves and points `IDYOM_KL_AUDIT_CONFIG` at a JSON config alongside the new `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/idyom_kl_audit_config.json.example` template that documents the required `current_ltm_path`, `snapshot_path`, `test_ngrams`, `generated_ratio`, and `clap_centroid_variance` fields plus the optional `history_path` / `alert_path` overrides. Test coverage in `tests/test_generation_health.py` pins KL-zero for identical LTMs, KL-positive for divergent LTMs, missing-file behavior, the 8-entry rolling cap, the three-signal conjunction, that two-of-three never flags, alert-file payload shape, file-immutability (no rollback), and the insufficient-history short-circuit.
CHANGELOG.md:7:- Wired `GenerationQueue` into the generation pipeline: updated its constructor to accept pipeline dependencies (`client`, `cache`, `budget`, `storage`) and implemented a `process_one()` method acting as a single-iteration worker loop that dequeues an item, generates audio, stores it, and marks the job done or failed. Added an integration test to verify the end-to-end processing pipeline on a mock client and storage.
CHANGELOG.md:9:- Added generation queue claim transitions: `GenerationQueue.dequeue()` now atomically claims the oldest queued row in a single SQLite transaction, marks it `running`, increments `attempts`, and refreshes `updated_at`; `mark_done()` completes running items; and `mark_failed()` requeues transient failures until the retry budget is exhausted, then marks the item `failed`. New queue tests cover FIFO claim ordering, retry-on-failure, terminal failure, timestamp refreshes, and concurrent no-double-claim behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:11:- Added a live Replicate smoke test for the generation backend (T-005): `tests/test_generation_live_replicate.py` exercises `ReplicateClient.generate(req)` against the real Replicate API with a fixed prompt and seed, and asserts a >100 KB WAV payload, `cost_usd` inside `[$0.01, $0.50]`, and `latency_ms < 60000`. The test is gated behind both the new `--run-live-replicate` pytest flag (registered in `tests/conftest.py` alongside the existing `--run-live-modal` seam) and a non-empty `REPLICATE_API_TOKEN`, so the default `pytest tests/` run skips it. Documented as ~$0.10 per opted-in run.
CHANGELOG.md:15:- Implemented `ModalClient` satisfying `GenerationClient` Protocol in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_modal.py`, enabling CypherClaw to use Modal serverless for generation (CCG-012). The client computes A10G runtime cost from metadata and gracefully degrades when the `modal` SDK is not installed. Also added protocol parity tests and gated live Modal tests behind `--run-live-modal`.
CHANGELOG.md:17:- Added a manifest-driven CCS-032 library migration path: `my-claw/tools/sample_library_import.py` now imports single files and directory buckets into `samples/library/`, `senseweave.sample_library.SampleRecord` / `SampleLibrary` now preserve full-record provenance via serialized record storage (including `extras.original_path` and `extras.captured_by`), `tests/test_sample_library_import.py` locks the importer contract, `sample_manifests/anthony-library.toml` captures Anthony's real 101-sample migration plan, and the resulting local library import is kept out of git via `.gitignore`.
CHANGELOG.md:23:- Wired active-song human phrase capture into the live listeners: new `senseweave.phrase_capture_runtime.ActiveSongPhraseCapture` gates `PhraseCaptureWriter` on fresh `/tmp/composer_state.json` song context, `midi_keyboard_listener.py` and `theramini_listener.py` now feed qualifying >5s phrases into `samples/keyboard/` and `samples/theramini/` with validated song/key/tempo sidecars, `PhraseCaptureWriter` now exposes `reset()` for safe song-boundary drops, and `human_phrase_capture_verify.py` plus new runtime/integration tests simulate both sources without hardware and validate the resulting paths and tags.
CHANGELOG.md:24:- Added a piece-aware sampler cast-planning seam: `senseweave.cast_planner` now exposes `assemble_cast(...)`, which derives selector kwargs from a piece fixture (`mode`, `arc_phase`, `mood`, `target_character`/`patch_name`), returns assembled cast entries, and mirrors any pre-selected sampler summary onto the sampler cast entry as `sample_record`; sampler summaries now also derive `duration_sec` from capture-shaped records via `frame_count / sample_rate`, and `duet_composer._get_cast()` now routes through the shared cast assembler. Added regression coverage in `tests/test_cast_planner.py` for fixture-piece planning and capture-shaped sample summaries, while keeping the targeted `cast_planner` + `sampler_dispatch` suites green.
CHANGELOG.md:25:- Added `my-claw/tools/sample_capture_service_verify.py` plus `tests/test_sample_capture_service_verify.py` as a repo-backed operational verifier for `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`: it checks `active/running` state, confirms the `cypherclaw-jack.service` dependency, and proves `Restart=always` recovery by forcing a `kill -9` and waiting for a new PID. Verified live on `cypherclaw` on April 25, 2026 with the daemon restarting from PID `1677354` to `1719358`.
CHANGELOG.md:26:- Deployed `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` to the live CypherClaw host: installed the repo-backed unit at `/etc/systemd/system/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`, ran `systemctl daemon-reload`, then `systemctl enable --now cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`. The service is now `enabled` and `active (running)` under systemd supervision with its `cypherclaw-jack.service` dependency satisfied, so `sample_capture_daemon.py` survives reboots and crash restarts without manual intervention.
CHANGELOG.md:27:- Added repo-backed sample-capture service wiring for the sampler rollout: `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` now runs `sample_capture_daemon.py` as `User=user` from the project virtualenv with `Restart=always`, `LimitMEMLOCK=infinity`, and `After`/`Requires` on `cypherclaw-jack.service`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now best-effort starts that service after the AV stack comes up; and `tests/test_cypherclaw_boot_runtime.py` pins both the unit-file contract and the boot-script hook.
CHANGELOG.md:29:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
CHANGELOG.md:30:- Updated `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to describe the active quintet direction: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`, and the new `sw_sampler` memory voice; the roadmap now separates landed sampler modules (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `sampler_effects.scd`, anti-pattern checks) from still-pending identity/library/SynthDef convergence so the documentation matches the tree's real partial-rollout state.
CHANGELOG.md:31:- Wired sample auto-tagging into the capture write path: `sample_capture_daemon.py` now exposes a stdlib-only `save_capture()` helper that writes mono 24-bit WAV captures, emits contextual + acoustic tags via `build_sample_tags()`, and persists both flattened tag fields and JSON payloads into `index.sqlite`; `tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py` now covers room/contextual tag emission, sample-index persistence, and percussive contact-capture indexing.
CHANGELOG.md:33:- Hardened sampler buffer cap enforcement: `BufferLoader` now rejects non-positive capacities, routes overflow eviction through `on_sampler_free()` before issuing new `/b_alloc` + `/b_allocRead` traffic, and has a regression test that fills the default 64-buffer pool and verifies the full load/evict cycle.
CHANGELOG.md:45:- Added artistic identity portfolio reporting and surface snapshots: new `portfolio_report.py` module provides `derive_portfolio_report()` for comprehensive identity summaries from repertoire metrics, preferred forms/modes, motif counts, practice block coverage with EMSD course codes, growth-state keys, and ear quality averages; and `derive_surface_snapshot()` for face/operator display data (current song title, section caption, practice block, artistic-intent line). Graceful degradation handles empty repertoire, missing fields, corrupt score trees, and absent growth state without hallucinating data.
CHANGELOG.md:46:- Added installation-aware acoustic ecology policies: new `acoustic_ecology.py` module provides `resolve_acoustic_ecology()` which translates presence, cadence, day phase, room activity, attention state, and dwell time into a frozen `AcousticEcologyPolicy` with hard ceilings for volume, onset density, and spectral brightness, silence window parameters, ordered source preferences, keynote privilege weights, and density/voice caps. Sleep and wind-down modes enforce non-negotiable ceilings that cannot be overridden by any modifier. Performance attention overrides wind-down constraints when the human is actively engaged. Room activity boosts keynote privilege so the room's own soundscape is the acoustic content.
CHANGELOG.md:47:- Added live-buffer and sample-bank abstractions for SenseWeave inputs: new `live_buffer.py` module provides `LiveBuffer` for stable real-time environmental audio state (source name, capture path, freshness, RMS, spectral profile, transform history) and `SampleBankArchive` for retaining selected clips to archive storage with JSON metadata sidecars.
CHANGELOG.md:52:- Fixed the long-section tracker compile bug that was turning songs into isolated sustained tones: `tracker_compiler.py` now converts large section budgets into repeat counts plus modest note-length scaling, and `music_tracker.py` quantizes those repeats into real repeated phrase cycles instead of stretching a handful of notes across the whole scene.
CHANGELOG.md:58:- Fixed transition metadata through motif recall: recalled `Recap` / `Release` lanes now strip stale source-scene transition fields and attach the current scene's own transition target to their final preparation tail.
CHANGELOG.md:63:- Fixed a live capture fallback issue that made the sampler lean on a quiet self bus: `room_listener.py` now skips absent named JACK ports and tries direct `jack_rec` fallback ports such as `system:capture_1`, while `sample_dsp_activity.py` now resolves missing `theramini_in` to `contact_mic` / `room_mic` before `self_bus`.
CHANGELOG.md:68:- Moved heavy runtime storage toward the large archive volume: added `archive_paths.py`, taught `sample_playback_engine.py` and `archive_daemon.py` to resolve a shared archive root (preferring `/mnt/archive/cypherclaw` on the live box), updated `cypherclaw_boot.sh` to put porch/side capture rings on that archive root, and reconfigured the live host so Litestream observatory/state file replicas live off the root disk with a much tighter observatory snapshot retention window.
CHANGELOG.md:71:- Hardened the local webcam path: `observer_vision.py` now defaults to `/dev/video0`, records `video_device`, and rejects stale old JPEGs when `ffmpeg` capture fails; `room_presence_daemon.py` can now run in `--observer-frame-only` mode and report `capture_source: "observer_frame"` so presence can share the single observer webcam instead of contending for it.
CHANGELOG.md:72:- Mirrored the shared observer frame back into `/tmp/room_frame.jpg` when `room_presence_daemon.py` is running in `--observer-frame-only` mode, so archive and room-frame consumers stay fresh instead of freezing on the last independent room-camera capture.
CHANGELOG.md:75:- Made the self-monitor more truthful: `self_listener.py` now derives glyph-facing brightness and motion from captured audio features instead of target-only metadata, while `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` pins the live meter to the verified JACK path on CypherClaw and still leaves PipeWire / `pw-jack` capture as fallback code paths.
CHANGELOG.md:76:- Fixed the remaining live self-monitor blackout path: when direct `jack_rec` capture times out, `self_listener.py` now falls back to analyzing a fresh `/tmp/room_capture.wav` clip instead of writing a dark `capture_timeout` state, so glyph and sampler decisions stay audio-derived on boxes where the JACK recorder hangs.
CHANGELOG.md:78:- Extended hook phrasing into actual later-section pitch behavior: `score_from_mood()` now publishes hook answer-degree metadata, and `music_tracker.py` uses that data in `Recap` / `Release` / `Resolution` / `Afterglow` so later sections can answer harmonically as well as textually.
CHANGELOG.md:89:- Made `self_listener.py` backend-aware: it now auto-selects between `jack_rec` and `pw-jack jack_rec`, sets `JACK_NO_START_SERVER=1` on its capture probes to avoid waking an unwanted JACK server, and publishes `capture_backend` in `/tmp/self_listen.json` so operators can tell which live graph the meter is following.
CHANGELOG.md:90:- Hardened that backend selection for the real CypherClaw boot race: direct `jack_lsp` probes can now take longer without forcing a false `pw-jack` fallback, `self_listener.py` caches the last working backend and resets that cache after failed capture loops, its `jack_rec` capture path now discards child stdout/stderr instead of risking a blocked pipe and stale meter state, and `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now deduplicates stale `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` copies instead of letting old bad boot loops accumulate dozens of live daemons.
CHANGELOG.md:92:- Swapped the self-listener toward a host-stable monitor path: `self_listener.py` now prefers a PipeWire sink monitor target when one is available, still falls back to direct JACK or `pw-jack` port capture when needed, and keeps the old backend cache/reprobe logic only as fallback behavior instead of the primary live path.
CHANGELOG.md:99:- Rebalanced EMSD source authority toward the room in lived-in late phases: capstone `Convergence` and `Crystallization` now prefer `room_mic` outside `away_practice`, DSP scene focus follows that same room bias, and `sample_dsp_activity.py` can retarget a sparse late-phase `self_bus` request onto a fresh room capture while still preserving the original requested source in state for operator visibility.
CHANGELOG.md:100:- Fixed room-capture triggering so external sample sources no longer depend on `self_listener` RMS. `room_mic`, `contact_mic`, and `theramini_in` now trigger from their own live cues, while only `self_bus` remains gated by self-audio level.
CHANGELOG.md:102:- Made the sampler musically scene-aware instead of only transform-aware: `sample_dsp_activity.py` now emits scene profiles like `development_grains`, `theme_accents`, `recap_echo`, `divination_bed`, and `afterglow_residue`, and `sample_event_renderer.py` now changes duration, density, peak target, filtering, stretch, and echo geometry from those profiles so the room layer follows the tracker form instead of using one generic behavior under different labels.
CHANGELOG.md:103:- Promoted the Perform-VE room mic to the actual live capture path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `room_listener.py` without `--no-jack`, and `room_listener.py` now reports `capture_backend` / `capture_source` so the live state shows whether JACK on the condenser path or an ALSA fallback is in use.
CHANGELOG.md:104:- Adjusted room-listener fallback priority so ALSA auto-selection now prefers the Perform-VE interface over webcam or generic analog capture when JACK is unavailable.
CHANGELOG.md:105:- Made room-listener ALSA capture more resilient by retrying alternate sample formats on each candidate device before falling through to the next one.
CHANGELOG.md:107:- Rebased the EMSD ambient default onto the real room condenser path: Divination/capstone planning and DSP source focus now prefer `room_mic` instead of `garden_mic`, so the default ambient sampler matches the Perform-VE microphone actually present on CypherClaw.
CHANGELOG.md:108:- Made EMSD sample activity resilient to missing sources: `sample_dsp_activity.py` can now resolve a requested source like `garden_mic` onto a fresh room/contact/self capture when the requested alias is unavailable, and `self_listener.py` now publishes a full capture registry so that fallback can happen from live file freshness instead of hardcoded guesswork.
CHANGELOG.md:109:- Wired stable EMSD sample capture into the live runtime: added `capture_alias.py` plus `sample_dsp_activity.py`, taught `room_listener.py`, `contact_listener.py`, `theramini_listener.py`, and `self_listener.py` to mirror fresh clips into `/tmp/room_capture.wav`, `/tmp/contact_capture.wav`, `/tmp/theramini_capture.wav`, and `/tmp/self_capture.wav`, and made `self_listener.py` publish `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` with concrete activity modes, trigger flags, and DSP/sample-control values derived from composer, cadence, and sensor state.
CHANGELOG.md:111:- Fed EMSD production plans into actual tracker playback: added `emsd_performance.py`, wired `duet_composer.py` to apply live mix/sample/DSP adjustments at the note boundary, extended `composer_emsd_extras()` with concrete sample capture metadata, and made the strongest top register fold down harder so notes above roughly `C6` are lowered an octave and the sharpest band is lowered two octaves.
CHANGELOG.md:113:- Built the first end-to-end EMSD package: added a 40-course curriculum catalog plus generated `my-claw/curriculum/EMSD-*` scaffolds, and implemented `sound_palette_lab.py`, `sample_lab.py`, `mix_engine.py`, `procedural_arc.py`, `dsp_scene_lab.py`, `artistic_identity.py`, and `capstone_engine.py` so the electronic music production roadmap now exists as runnable code and tests instead of only a brief.
CHANGELOG.md:118:- Made face captions orchestration-aware: `prosody_engine.py` now uses `patch_name` and lane count so sparse scenes compress hook language while denser scenes widen it into fuller face text.
CHANGELOG.md:119:- Made face captions harmonic-function-aware: `prosody_engine.py` now uses `cadence_type` for `Resolution` and `Afterglow`, so the same hook can resolve differently under dominant, plagal, authentic, and deceptive harmonic landings.
CHANGELOG.md:120:- Added legacy repertoire hook repair: `repertoire_memory.py` now normalizes broken historical hook text like `answer the again` on load and store, so old artifacts stop leaking into new songs and captions.
CHANGELOG.md:121:- Made scene captions section-aware: `prosody_engine.py` now reshapes the same hook differently for `Theme`, `Recap`/`Release`, and `Resolution`/`Afterglow`, so face text follows the song arc instead of repeating one caption verbatim.
CHANGELOG.md:126:- Built the first complete M1-M6 musicianship package end to end: added `reharmonizer.py`, `hook_engine.py`, `arrangement_engine.py`, `ear_engine.py`, `practice_curriculum.py`, `prosody_engine.py`, and `repertoire_memory.py`; extended `harmonic_planner.py`, `generative_scores.py`, `music_tracker.py`, `continuous_learner.py`, `duet_composer.py`, and `keyboard_chat.py` so tracker songs now carry section functions, cadence types, hook metadata, scene arrangement intent, practice-block focus, ear-metric evaluation, repertoire storage, and face-visible song titles/captions through the live runtime.
CHANGELOG.md:133:- Added scene-level tracker recall inside each song: `build_korsakov_tracker_song()` now lets `Recap` and short-form `Release` borrow motif shapes from the already-built `Theme` scene with answering transforms and provenance metadata, so those sections feel like intentional returns instead of parallel re-renderings of the same score.
CHANGELOG.md:152:- Made CypherClaw tracker solo cast-aware: the live composer now derives tracker lane voice hints from the active character cast and enforces a quiet foundation lane through subdued `Theme`/`Development`/`Recap` scenes.
CHANGELOG.md:193:- Added Decision Store for Architecture Decision Records (ADRs) with keyword-based retrieval.
CHANGELOG.md:217:- Added agent roster customization and capability inference during startup.
