sdp/verification/t-018@20260425t183959zd-verify.md:41:One implementation note: the keyboard `capture_chunk` accumulates raw bytes across all MIDI devices in a single loop tick before being fed. This is correct — note-on/note-off timing from multiple simultaneous device reads lands in the same SMF chunk.
sdp/verification/t-018@20260425t183959zd-verify.md:45:Follows the established repo pattern for deterministic verification scripts (`sample_capture_verify.py`, `composer_quote_verify.py`, `self_listener_quote_verify.py`). The `capture_phrase_from_state` helper functions mirror the naming pattern of `apply_phrase_tracker` already in theramini_listener. The `ActiveSongPhraseCapture` class wraps `PhraseCaptureWriter` cleanly without coupling the listeners to sidecar metadata internals, consistent with the single-responsibility approach used in the existing capture subsystem.
sdp/verification/t-018@20260425t183959zd-verify.md:49:No new security surface introduced. All file I/O is bounded to the configured capture root. The composer state reader (`_read_json`) silently returns an empty dict on any `OSError` or `JSONDecodeError`, preventing crashes from malformed or inaccessible state files. Sidecar schema validation is applied on every write. No new dependencies added.
sdp/verification/t-018@20260425t183959zd-verify.md:58:- `bootstrap_identity()` invocation: confirmed in both `my-claw/tools/daemon.py` (line 2462) and `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` (line 3542), both before `FirstBootAnnouncer`. Out of scope for this listener-capture task; existing coverage is current and clean.
