sdp/verification/t-012@20260425t183959zb-verify.md:14:The task requires: trigger the composer to run 3 pieces against a captured descriptor and verify at least one self-quotes the sample (motif/tag match logged).
sdp/verification/t-012@20260425t183959zb-verify.md:16:The LEAD agent delivers exactly this: `composer_quote_verify.py` captures a known room descriptor via `capture_known_room_sound()`, drives 3 simulated post-piece `self_quote()` calls against a fake JACK self-bus pre-loaded with the same room tone, then calls `find_motif_tag_match()` to confirm at least one resulting `samples/self/` row shares both `arc_phase` and `acoustic_tags` overlap with the original descriptor.
sdp/verification/t-012@20260425t183959zb-verify.md:18:The self-quote trigger gate in `sample_capture_daemon._should_self_quote()` requires `arc_payoff > 0.6`, `click_count == 0`, and `mode != working_ambience`. The `_piece_score_summary()` helper sets `arc_payoff=0.85`, `click_count=0`, `mode="solo"` — all gate conditions are satisfied, so all 3 pieces trigger a capture. The tag/arc match is confirmed by `find_motif_tag_match()` which requires both `arc_phase` equality and non-empty acoustic tag overlap.
sdp/verification/t-012@20260425t183959zb-verify.md:31:Missing edge case: no test for `main()` exit code 1 (zero self-quotes captured). Not blocking — the monkeypatching approach used in test 5 covers the no-match path; a zero-capture path would require stubbing `trigger_composer_pieces` and is a minor gap.
