sdp/verification/t-028@20260427t001208z-verify.md:17:- Eviction loop uses `_over_limits()` which checks both entry count and byte sum; whichever cap fires first triggers eviction of the LRU (min `accessed_at`).
sdp/verification/t-028@20260427t001208z-verify.md:33:- Dataclass for internal state, top-level private helpers, `__all__` export — consistent with `budget.py` from T-027.
sdp/verification/t-028@20260427t001208z-verify.md:46:Code is clean and idiomatic. The `_evict_if_needed` loop correctly handles the "whichever cap hits first" requirement. The `_prune_missing` pass on startup prevents stale index entries from inflating the byte count. Injected `clock` makes tests deterministic without monkey-patching. No comments beyond the module docstring — appropriate.
sdp/verification/t-028@20260427t001208z-verify.md:50:The SDP runner injected recurring failure patterns about `bootstrap_identity` and `FirstBootAnnouncer`. These belong to daemon startup flow (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `cypherclaw_daemon.py`) and are **not applicable** to `GenerationCache`, which is a pure library module with no startup lifecycle. No action required here.
