sdp/verification/t-010@20260425t183959z-verify.md:11:The implementation accurately follows the requirements. `duet_composer.py` calls `sample_capture_daemon.self_quote` with the correct gate conditions (`arc_payoff > 0.6`, `click_count == 0`, `mode != working_ambience`). The daemon captures a 4-second window centered on the peak absolute value from `SuperCollider:out_1` and saves it to `samples/self/` with all required tags.
sdp/verification/t-010@20260425t183959z-verify.md:22:The code follows existing patterns in the codebase, particularly the use of `NumpyRingBuffer` and the unified tagging system in `sample_capture_daemon.py`.
sdp/verification/t-010@20260425t183959z-verify.md:28:The code is well-structured and includes comprehensive tests. The integration between the composer and the capture daemon is decoupled via a try-except block to prevent capture failures from interrupting the music loop.
sdp/verification/t-010@20260425t183959z-verify.md:31:- [x] Hardening: `bootstrap_identity()` is correctly invoked in the startup flow of `sample_capture_daemon.py`.
sdp/verification/t-010@20260425t183959z-verify.md:36:The implementation is solid. The centering logic for the self-quotation window is particularly robust, ensuring the most salient part of the song is captured.
